Summary
Tables are best used when presenting structured data, while <div> elements are preferred for flexible layouts that require more control and responsiveness. Understanding the right context for each element is key to creating efficient, visually appealing web pages.

Conclusion:

While tables can be used for simple layouts, <div> elements with CSS provide more flexibility and control over the layout and styling of your web pages. For most modern web development, it's recommended to use <div> elements and CSS to create responsive and accessible designs.